==Translingual==
===Cardinal number===
*[[w:Arabic numerals|Arabic numerals]]: 0
*[[w:Chinese numerals|Chinese numerals]]: [[零]], [[〇]]

===Pronunciation===
''See'' [[zero]]

====Pronunciation note====
In certain areas, to save time or to keep a rhythm in pronouncing repeated [[digit]]s, the pronunciation of zero is often shortened to that of the letter '''[[o|O]]'''. This is common in saying [[telephone number]]s, or words such as "[[w:007|007]]".

===Noun===
'''0''' (''plural:'' '''[[0s]]''')
# The [[cardinal number]] [[zero]] indicating absence of any quantity. 
#:''They scored '''0''' in their worst game yet.''
# [[numeral]] corresponding to the number zero.
#:''The flashing '''0''' indicates that time is up.''
# A [[digit]] in [[decimal]], [[binary]], and every other [[base]] numbering system.
#:''The Boolean domain contains only '''0''' and 1.''
#:''Hexadecimal numbers ending in '''0''' are divisible by 16.''
# The origin, starting point, or fixed reference point, especially for a measurement.
#:''The '''0''' for the Celcius scale is 273.15 Kelvin.''
# Nothing, nought.
#:''The shipment was lost, so they had '''0''' in stock.''
#{{mathematics}} The [[identity element]] with respect to [[addition]].
#: <math>\exists\,\mathbf{0}:\forall a\in A:\mathbf{0}+a=a+\mathbf{0}=a</math>

====Synonyms====
*number: [[cipher]], [[nil]], [[nought]], [[null]]
*digit: [[slashed zero]]

====Derived terms====
*[[0th]], the [[ordinal number]] form
*[[10]], [[20]], [[100]], etc. cardinal number representations containing [[digit]] '''0'''.

===Adjective===
'''0'''
# Of no or zero quantity; of [[cardinality]] zero.
#:''In the desert '''0''' cm precipitation per month is common.''
#Of the origin, starting point, especially for a measurement.
#:''The ice will begin to melt at '''0''' degrees C.''

